02/09/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Labour Minister Rasim Ljajic, who currently heads the Sandzak Democratic Party (SDP), submitted on Tuesday (September 1st) about 11,500 signatures needed to register a new party, the Social Democratic Party of Serbia. Ljajic said he will head the new party and that the SDP will continue to function at the local and regional level, and will partner with the new party in the next elections, scheduled for May 2012. He added that the new party will also aim to clinch a co-operation agreement with the main members of the ruling coalition -- the Democratic Party and the Socialist Party of Serbia. (B92, Blic, Tanjug - 01/09/09)
